The Ministry of Finance can apply a combined tactic within the meaning of the law: it can simultaneously buy out low-quality loans, mortgages and securities secured by mortgages, or other "poisonous" loans, respectively.
The purchase can take place within the framework of auctions and directly, the competent representatives of the Ministry said.
The legal norm will allow the companies concerned to participate in the insurance program, in which the Ministry of Finance will provide them with a guarantee on the funds that constitute a cause for concern, for which the companies will then pay a price corresponding to the amount of the expected damage.
As Henry Paulson said, the law provides the necessary means to spend up to $700 billion to meet the urgent requirements of the U.S. financial system, whether it’s a large-scale purchase of bad funds, their insurance, or to prevent systemic risk associated with the collapse of one of the major financial institutions.
"We will take the necessary steps to be ready to implement the law as soon as it is signed," he added.
