Restrictions on their payments will only occur in certain cases, in addition, these restrictions will depend on the manner of assistance provided by the Ministry.
The restriction basically means that if the Ministry buys under the auction, a tax surcharge will be imposed on the gold parachute unless the fallen directors of the banks are sent straight to retirement.
In the case of the direct purchase of low-quality loans, the government will aggressively intervene in order to ensure that the money for management is not exaggerated.
It is necessary to add that the existing contracts for gold traps will not change, the restrictions apply only to new contracts, which should be another incentive to participate in the programme.
