Export sales prices in the industry were higher by 1.1 per cent compared to July 2008 and decreased by 3.9 per cent year-on-year.
As a result of changes in domestic and export prices, industrial production prices were 0.7 per cent higher compared to the previous month and rose by 3.2 per cent year-on-year.
Domestic sales prices in the industry increased by just 0.1 per cent compared to the previous month.
Domestic sales prices in the manufacturing sector also increased slightly, by 0.1 per cent, compared to July.
