"This material could be useful as a temporary adhesive," adds Liming Dai.
Perhaps to walk on walls like Spiderman? Perhaps so, but researchers are thinking about far less fascinating uses as a combination of electrical appliances, because dwarf carbon tubes are conductors of heat and electricity.
Other applications could relate to aerospace engineering .
