The arrests this morning follow a July arrest last year that police showed that the Mafia group Piromalli had received a final crackdown.
Since the end of April last year - the city council of Gioiia Tauro had been dissolved since 1991, the reason for this was the supposed link between organized crime and local administration - local politicians were deprived of office in the municipal administration.
Giorgio Dal Torrione, president of the Christian Democrats, who was elected head of the centre-right coalition at the time of the dissolution after narrower elections in May.
He was screaming about a scandal when the prefecture ordered the dissolution of the municipal council.
