Experts are talking about the technology, which is still in its infancy, because it is not known what impact the use of marine energy will have on the environment.
For now, facilities in Portugal and some in Scotland are small in size and do not seem to cause major ecosystem problems.
However, for greater energy production, it is necessary to use technologies with a greater impact on the dilution.
